{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An enclosed group of covalently bonded atoms."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MM4RigidBody"}],"externalID":"s:3MM40A9RigidBodyV","title":"MM4RigidBody","roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"MM4"}],"symbolKind":"struct","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MM4RigidBody","kind":"identifier"}]},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/init(parameters:)"]},{"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/angularVelocity","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/centerOfMass","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/externalForces","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/linearVelocity","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/mass","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/momentOfInertia","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/parameters","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/positions","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/vectorizedPositions","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/vectorizedVelocities","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/velocities"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/getPositions(_:)","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/getVelocities(_:)","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/setPositions(_:)-399k0","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/setPositions(_:)-73bjz","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/setThermalKineticEnergy(temperature:heatCapacity:)","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/setVelocities(_:)-5rrj7","doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/setVelocities(_:)-92eox"],"title":"Instance Methods"}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"MM4RigidBody","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MM4RigidBody"},{"text":" is an API to efficiently compute basic properties in rigid","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"body mechanics. Specifically, a non-consecutive memory layout optimized for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the vector units on modern CPUs.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This documentation page is still a draft. It may be inconsistent or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"difficult to understand.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The rigid body exists caches the vectorized layout for positions\/velocities","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and efficiently computes properties like moment of inertia."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It also efficiently initializes thermal velocities. The user is welcome to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"create their own data structure wrapping ‘MM4Parameters’, which avoids the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conversion from Vec3 to a swizzled representation. They could also make such"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"data structures only for a tiny fraction of atoms that require more"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"fine-grained access to mutating elements. If such an API were created in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"MM4, it would have no purpose. There needs to be some kind of unique"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functionality provided by the code in MM4, such as very optimized methods"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for computing certain properties + CoW caching. Stuff that would be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"extremely difficult or tedious to create manually."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Need performance (API similar to OpenMM, which requires positions and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"velocities to be set in batches):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"MM4RigidBody"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"API for copying positions\/velocities from an atom range to a rigid body"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Need flexibility:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom data structure storing an MM4Parameters, along with some positions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and velocities."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Can even wrap a rigid body, just with custom or more ergonomic methods to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"access the positions. Or not; set Vec3 into OpenMM directly if that for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"some reason has greater performance.","type":"text"}]}]}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/mm4\/mm4rigidbody"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://MM4/documentation/MM4/MM4RigidBody/linearVelocity":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/MM4\/documentation\/MM4\/MM4RigidBody\/linearVelocity","kind":"symbol","title":"linearVelocity","url":"\/documentation\/mm4\/mm4rigidbody\/linearvelocity","abstract":[{"text":"T